<HEADLINE>#84m aid boost for defence</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>3</EDITION>
<PAGE>2</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>974766081</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
BRITISH regions which are highly dependent on the hard-pressed defence industry
have won #84m of European aid, it was announced yesterday.
The Scottish Office has the list of areas north of the Border which will
benefit from the windfall.
Those eligible for grants include, Argyll and Bute, Cunninghame, Glasgow, parts
of Fife, and Edinburgh.
The grants will be used to help industry diversify and to strengthen the local
economic base.
The so-called Konver II programme targets small and medium-sized companies that
need help with innovation, know-how, and training.
Support will also be given to improvements to the environment, tourism
projects, and the restoration of military and defence industry sites.
Industry Energy Minister Tim Eggar welcomed the announcement as good news for
areas dependent on defence.
``These funds are particularly important in the drive to diversify and
strengthen the economic base of the areas concerned,'' he said.
</TEXT>
