Holiday tragedy
MADRID: A French lorry driver failed a breathalyser test yesterday after his
truck collided head-on with a van, killing eight Portuguese emigrant workers on
their way home for Christmas. Four others in the van were gravely injured. The
32-year-old trucker was nearly twice over the limit after the crash near
Vitoria in northern Spain, police said.
Stalin honoured
MOSCOW: Scattered groups of Russian Stalinists braved a snowstorm in Red Square
to place flowers on their hero's grave yesterday, the 116th anniversary of his
birth. A small group of mostly elderly members of the hardline All-Union
Communist Party (Bolshevik), who boycotted last Sunday's parliamentary
election, laid a wreath and flowers on the grave in Red Square.
