<DOCNO>GH951222-000020</DOCNO>
<DOCID>GH951222-000020</DOCID>
<DATE>951222</DATE>
<HEADLINE>New leads in murder hunt</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>3</EDITION>
<PAGE>9</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>974766101</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
A YOUNG woman was followed near where murdered Kilmarnock schoolgirl Mhairi
Julyan was last seen alive, police revealed yesterday.
The woman, who is in her twenties, was tracked on London Road, Kilmarnock. The
incident happened in darkness on Wednesday last week, just three days before
16-year-old Mhairi's killing.
It also emerged yesterday that a mystery caller who phoned police could have
vital information.
The man leading the murder hunt, Detective Chief Inspector Bob Lauder, said:
``A woman was walking in London Road at about 5.30pm last Wednesday when she
realised she was being followed.
``That's obviously of interest to us and we are anxious to hear from anyone who
had a similar experience in that area, or who has any information.''
The man, who is thought to be 5ft 2in tall, was in his early twenties with dark
brown, collar-length wavy hair, light stubble, and a sallow expression. He was
wearing a brown leather jacket.
No words were spoken and the man disappeared after the woman, who police are
not identifying, turned off London Road.
DCI Lauder also revealed that a witness had phoned police with information
about a sighting of Mhairi walking in London Road shortly before 10pm on
Saturday. He urged the person to call again.
</TEXT>
</DOC>
