<HEADLINE>Total satisfaction is company aim</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>Wendy Jack</BYLINE>
<EDITION>1</EDITION>
<PAGE>30</PAGE>
<ARTICLETYPE>Advertising Feature</ARTICLETYPE>
<GRAPHIC>Photograph</GRAPHIC>
<RECORDNO>974766159</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
BRAND names are synonymous with the Vogue name, but at discounted prices. The
customer therefore has the confidence inspired by a recognised name of quality,
allied to competitive price tags.
Among the best known labels to be seen within the showroom are: Ercol, Stag,
Beaver &amp; Tapley, Nathan, Strongbow, Morris, Ducal, McIntosh, Wade, Cintique,
Duresta, Parker Knoll in furniture. In carpets, well respected names such as
Stoddard, Templeton, Mr Tomkinson, Kosset, Wilton Royal, Ulster, Brintons, are
just a few of the many ranges available. Similarly in the bed department in
hall three, where bedroom furniture ranges, are also displayed, you'll find
Rest Assured, Sealy, Slumberland, Silentnight and Relyon.
Here too, is where the custom-made curtain department is housed with an
excellent selection of fabrics from some of the leading manufacturers. Whatever
your ideas, for beautiful curtains and headings, this is where they can be
turned into practical possibilities. A home measuring service is available.
With around 120 three-piece suites on display at prices ranging from #699 to
#4000, more than 40 full dining ranges on view (wall units from #599 to #4500);
more than 26 full bedroom ranges displayed, and around 24 sofa bed styles to
see, customers' greatest difficulty will be making a choice.
There's lots of variety too in occasional pieces of furniture, with some really
interesting ideas such as handsome wooden topped tables with wrought iron
underframes; slender metal-framed pieces teamed with glass and canework, and
the unusual but effective looks of metal with verdigris finish.
``There used to be a tremendous difference between the European and American
markets, and the British and American tastes but they are all tending to
converge now,'' comments Robert Bremner.
He believes Vogue's new showroom is Glasgow's biggest furniture store, and, he
said: ``We believe in offering excellent customer service - while always being
pleased to allow people to browse in peace. We are fairly unique in the
furniture industry as far as independents go in that we have a fully
computerised system. We reckon that we are more efficient than anybody else in
Scotland because of it. The programme was written specifically for us and we've
had lots of people coming up from the South to look at it.''
Huge choice of quality products; branded names, often at significant discounts;
up to 36 months' interest-free credit - dependent upon the size of the order; a
promise that they won't be beaten on price; and customer care which extends
through delivery until the customer is fully satisfied with their products . .
. are the main reasons why Vogue considers itself the No.1 choice when it comes
to house furnishers.
</TEXT>
