<HEADLINE>Shelley wins top award</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>2</EDITION>
<PAGE>23</PAGE>
<GRAPHIC>Photograph</GRAPHIC>
<RECORDNO>974766161</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
SHELLEY Wright has been named Young Journalist of the Year by the Guild of
Agricultural Journalists. She works in London for Farmers Weekly.
Shelley, whose parents now live at Thornhill in Dumfriesshire, was born in
Glasgow but brought up in Aberdeen.
After gaining a BSc honours degree in animal science at Nottingham University
she sold animal health products before becoming communications manager for the
then Scottish Milk Marketing Board.
She took up her present post last year, specialising in livestock and milk
issues.
</TEXT>
