<HEADLINE>McLevy steps up</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>2</EDITION>
<PAGE>32</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>974766179</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
SCOTTISH champion Steve McLevy steps up in class next month, when he tops the
bill at the St Andrew's Sporting Club, Glasgow.
The hard-hitting Scotstoun light-welterweight opens the new season on January
22 against former British super-featherweight champion Dramani ``Sugar''
Gibiliru.
The 29-year-old Scouser with more than 60 campaigns against the best in Europe,
last fought in Glasgow eight years ago when he shared a draw with Helensburgh's
Robert Harkin.
q.CHATHAM'S Johnny Armour must defend his European bantamweight title against
Denmark's Johnny Bredahl by March 15.
Bredahl has been brought in as Armour's challenger after the withdrawal of
Scotland's Drew Docherty as the No.1 contender, and the European Boxing Union
have ordered a purse offer deadline of January 16 for the new fight.
