<TEXT>
YOUR article headed ``Scottish Milk upbeat'' on December 20 contained an
inaccuracy.
The quoted Milk Marque price is out of date. Milk Marque has been paying
members a higher price of 25ppl, based on a standard litre of 4.1% butterfat
and 3.3% protein since October. This resulted in an increase in the price
received by members of nearly 0.5ppl.
A bonus of 0.3ppl has been paid on milk supplied between April and October this
year, with an intention to pay a similar bonus for November to March. The
majority of members also receive a bonus of 0.22ppl for producing milk with low
cell counts.
--Andrew Dare,
--chief executive,
--Milk Marque.
</TEXT>
