<EDITION>2</EDITION>
<PAGE>33</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>974766185</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
MORE than 1000 policemen will be on riot duty at tomorrow's eagerly awaited
top-of-the-table clash between Fiorentina and AC Milan in Florence.
Live television coverage of the serie A game for the entire Tuscany region is
expected, while the expected 2000 Milan fans will be escorted to and from the
ground.
League leaders Milan come into the game one point ahead of Fiorentina, with
Parma a further point away in third and Juventus fourth, five behind Milan.
Fiorentina's notoriously explosive fans are hoping that their side can knock
Milan off the top of the table, but their shrewd coach Claudio Ranieri
dismisses talk of his side winning the title. He insists that qualifying for
the UEFA Cup is his priority.
Fiorentina's Argentine striker Gabriel Batistuta also tried to play down the
significance of the game. ``One match, even an important one, won't make us
lose our heads,'' he said.
</TEXT>
