<HEADLINE>Seven on sidelines</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>2</EDITION>
<PAGE>33</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>974766188</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
HAMILTON are facing a selection crisis that could mean their revival lasts just
90 minutes. The first division basement side have four players suspended and
three injured for the Boxing Day clash at Dundee United.
Paul Hartley, Paul McKenzie, Gary Clark and Stephen McInulty are banned with
crocked trio Martin McIntosh, John McQuade and Scott McCulloch joining them on
the sidelines.
Accies beat Dumbarton 3-0 last week, but assistant manager Sandy Clark knows
the missing seven will make it doubly tough at Tannadice.
Clark said: ``We don't have problems to seek for available players and it will
certainly stretch our resources. It's a pity Hartley is missing because he has
been playing particularly well recently.
``Obviously, it will be very difficult against Dundee United, but we will go
and do our best.''
</TEXT>
