<HEADLINE>Dogged by thefts</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>2</EDITION>
<PAGE>23</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>974766193</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
THIEVES are on the run with a sheepdog which has starred in farming adverts and
is said to be worth #1000.
Sam, a three-year-old smooth-coated collie, was stolen while owner Tom Jones of
Trefeddian Farm, Aberdyfi, Gwynedd, took a tea-break on his farm. ``I was only
in the house for a quarter-of-an-hour and when I came back he had gone,'' he
said.
Police and farmers' organisations warned of a series of thefts. At least 10
dogs have disappeared so far this winter in the Aberdyfi and Bala areas of
North Wales. Some have also gone missing in North Ceredigion.
Melvyn Harrison, a regional official for AGF Insurance, said: ``With the
current spate of thefts, we would urge farmers to take extra care, locking up
their dogs safe at night and making sure they do not stray during the day.''
</TEXT>
