<TEXT>
q TRAINER Kim Bailey is not hoping for a white Christmas as he seeks to get
Master Oats back on the winning road.
The Gold Cup victor is pencilled in for next Thursday's Ericsson Chase at
Leopardstown as he tries to redeem a reputation tarnished by an inexplicable
flop at Chepstow earlier in the month.
But should wintry weather force the abandonment of Kempton's King George
programme on Boxing Day, Master Oats will challenge Merry Gale in the
three-mile Ericsson Chase.
Other possible rivals to Master Oats include the Galway Plate winner, Life of a
Lord, and last season's Greenalls Gold Cup winner, Nuaffe.
Bailey is still at a loss to explain Master Oats' poor performance in
Chepstow's Rehearsal Chase, when he was pulled up three out.
</TEXT>
