<HEADLINE>`Bishop' with roving eye to be extradited</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>2</EDITION>
<PAGE>4</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>974766201</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
A CON-MAN who posed as a Sicilian bishop and seduced two nuns is being returned
to Austria to face allegations of deception. Angelo Malannino, 46, of no fixed
abode, signed a document at Bow Street Magistrates' Court in London yesterday
waiving his right to contest extradition.
He was sentenced to jail on other theft offences at York Crown Court on
December 5, then released and re-arrested on the extradition warrant.
He is said to have convinced two nuns whose children he fathered that he was a
Roman Catholic priest and had been personally ordained by the Pope.
</TEXT>
