<HEADLINE>Too polite?</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>1</EDITION>
<PAGE>16</PAGE>
<ARTICLETYPE>Correspondence</ARTICLETYPE>
<RECORDNO>974766226</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
WHO invented the phrase ``drink driving''? Is this what we used to call ``drunk
driving''?
Is this a way of putting it more politely, lest we hurt the feelings of fools
who do it?
Moyna Gardner,
28 Hamilton Park Avenue,
Glasgow.
</TEXT>
