<HEADLINE>Oil spill</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>1</EDITION>
<PAGE>4</PAGE>
<FLAG>news digest</FLAG>
<RECORDNO>974766235</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
BP, operators of the Sullom Voe oil terminal in Shetland, reported yesterday
that two or three tonnes of oil had spilled from the tanker Alandia Wave from a
crack in one of the ship's tanks. A spokesman said oil pollution staff were
working on the spill.
Attacker fined
A TEENAGE girl who struck a man in the face with a glass tumbler in a
Kirkcudbright hotel has been fined #400 and ordered to pay her victim #400
compensation. At Kirkcudbright Sheriff Court yesterday, Elizabeth Girgan, 19,
of Memory Lane, Gatehouse of Fleet, admitted assaulting Mr Richard Baty, of
Millburn Street, Kirkcudbright, in the Gordon House Hotel.
Eye spy
BUSINESS people in Eyemouth are to consider introducing a closed-circuit
surveillance system in the town centre in a bid to reduce crime, following the
Scottish Office announcement that #4m is being made available to fund 1000
cameras in towns in Scotland.
Jobless ghost
MORE than 63,600 Scots are among 850,000 unemployed facing a second Christmas
without a job, according to a new TUC report entitled Unemployment: the Ghost
of Christmas Past and Present, published today. One in five long-term
unemployed are over 50.
</TEXT>
