<HEADLINE>Tenant resists `neighbours from hell'</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>1</EDITION>
<PAGE>4</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>974766237</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
IT will be lonely this Christmas for Abraham Baxter. He is refusing to move to
make way for a controversial scheme.
On Christmas Day, he will be home alone in St Clement's Terrace, Dundee - the
defiant last tenant in a tenement block scheduled to become a fortress to
rehabilitate ``neighbours from hell''.
Despite the noise and dust generated by workmen transforming the tenement into
a #1m high-security unit, Mr Baxter is sitting tight.
He said: ``I'm just sick of getting pushed around. The good tenants are having
to make way for the bad in this block.''
</TEXT>
